Dear sir/madam

Yet again I find myself having to contact you regarding my PURCHASED item.
I have STILL not received it! I am now becoming very very frustrated and
fed up with your company and the way that you operate also the fact that I
should received the item by now as it was ordered and PAID FOR mid November
2018. I am extremely disatisfied and will never purchase any item from
yourselves again. I expect my purchased item to reach myself by the end of
this week if it does not I will inform trading standards demand not only
the item but also a full refund as compensation to myself for all the
distress caused and is ongoing. I am within my full rights as a consumer to
take the said action above. The only response I get from your company is
that you are sorry and that my purchased item is on route to myself. This
is no longer acceptable and will no longer suffice as an answer or
response. I have even gone as far as telephoning the couriers to enquire as
to whether or not they have  my item in question but have had no joy
regarding this line of enquiry as they know nothing about it and do not not
have any records of the item on their systems. It has not only cost myself
wasted time but also money that came out of my personal account. I expect
this matter to be resolved one way or another by the end of this week by
yourselves.


Dione Green.

Dear Entrepreneur, 

Greetings and hope everything is fine at your end!

I’m holding a special insight for your business website: everyougo.com, where I’ll walk you through my ideas on “How to build a better income and create thousands of followers using Social Media accounts for your business”.


	Is your Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn accounts update daily basic?
	How to get influencers to promote your business?
	How to develop loyal/global fans?
	How to generate more leads?
	How to turn followers into paying clients?


Social Media represent a huge opportunity for businesses to grab customer relationship management, market research, customer base expansion and customer retention, product marketing, cost control initiatives, public relations etc.

If you are interested then let me know with your queries, so that I can send you the “Social Media Plan of Action” for your business by analyzing your current social media presence.

I am looking forward to hearing from you.

Thanks & Regards,
Lucy Roy
Senior Business Analyst

P.S:  This is a onetime email, and if you are not interested, just reply with “Unsubscribe”, and we’ll not contact you again.
